<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1749,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1899,1925]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body pale testaceous, superior part of face and frontal rostrum dark brown, lateral lobes of pronotum dark brown with yellowish inferior part, lateral field of tegmen with dark band. Vertex convex and eyes vertically lengthened, 
<number box="[470,483,1974,2000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="5.0">5</number>
th joint of maxillary palpi triangular. Tympana on both sides of fore tibiae and the inner one larger than outer one. Male genitalia with lateral processes slightly incurved (
<figureCitation box="[1174,1317,2011,2037]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,271,1243,1267]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,495,1206]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,495,1219]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 11. Amusurgus (Amusurgus) fulvus Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893. 9. face, frontal view; 10. genitalia of male, dorsal view; 11. genitalia of male, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Figs. 
<number box="[1240,1317,2011,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
